for the sand, for the beach...

486
00:49:54,320 --> 00:49:58,484
...but to put a hotel here,
it would cost a fortune.

487
00:50:00,994 --> 00:50:03,319
Do you know what?

488
00:50:03,496 --> 00:50:06,497
My bankers say I'm insane.

489
00:50:09,127 --> 00:50:13,789
God, in the right spot,
it would be fantastic!

490
00:50:31,107 --> 00:50:34,392
You always been impatient, lady?
I mean, your whole life?

491
00:50:34,569 --> 00:50:38,697
Mr. Shin, in four weeks
I've given you $600.

492
00:50:38,865 --> 00:50:41,534
You, by way of contrast,
have given me zip.

493
00:50:42,118 --> 00:50:45,202
I'm surprised you can find
your office in the morning.

494
00:50:45,371 --> 00:50:49,832
You always sarcastic like that?
You were sarcastic little baby?

495
00:50:50,001 --> 00:50:52,918
You look for lady for four weeks, huh?

496
00:50:53,087 --> 00:50:55,874
One time I look for somebody
for 18 years.

497
00:50:57,091 --> 00:50:58,918
Quite a recommendation.

498
00:50:59,593 --> 00:51:01,716
Persistence.

499
00:51:01,887 --> 00:51:06,715
Besides, can't find such a pretty lady
for buck and a half a week.

500
00:51:06,892 --> 00:51:10,226
- Need incentive bonus.
- No, just show me what you've got.

501
00:51:10,604 --> 00:51:12,763
What do you mean, huh?
I got nothing.

502
00:51:12,940 --> 00:51:16,107
Mr. Shin, any man that would ask me
for a price increase...

503
00:51:16,277 --> 00:51:19,646
...without anything to deliver
would be kind of stupid.

504
00:51:19,822 --> 00:51:22,028
No point in insulting
your intelligence.

505
00:51:22,241 --> 00:51:25,242
I'd rather do business on a basis
of mutual respect.

506
00:51:25,744 --> 00:51:27,618
That's good.

507
00:51:27,788 --> 00:51:30,279
- I like respect.
- Fine.

508
00:51:30,666 --> 00:51:32,125
Where is she?

509
00:51:32,459 --> 00:51:35,129
All right, ladies,
before we re-enter the pool...

510
00:51:35,295 --> 00:51:40,716
...let's review the most important rule:
Never race your bubbles to the surface.

511
00:51:40,884 --> 00:51:47,172
It can cause lung expansion, which
can result in air in the bloodstream.

512
00:51:47,349 --> 00:51:51,477
This can produce an embolism,
which can result in...

513
00:51:51,645 --> 00:51:55,228
- You all right? Maybe you should sit out.
- A very agonizing death.

514
00:51:57,234 --> 00:52:00,021
Now then, ladies, let's get in the pool.

515
00:52:06,618 --> 00:52:08,825
Good. Okay, ladies,
come around here.

516
00:52:09,037 --> 00:52:11,991
Come on. Come on, all of you.

517
00:52:12,165 --> 00:52:17,207
We're going to pair up and practice
breathing two on the same regulator.

518
00:52:17,379 --> 00:52:20,131
This would be necessary
when one runs out of air.

519
00:52:20,298 --> 00:52:22,587
Now pair up. You and you.
You and you.

520
00:52:23,009 --> 00:52:28,466
That's right. Take the regulator and give
it to your partner for emergency air.

521
00:52:28,640 --> 00:52:31,807
Partners? Don't worry.
I'm not really contagious.

522
00:52:31,977 --> 00:52:35,926
My friend promised me she'd
be my partner, so...

523
00:52:36,147 --> 00:52:40,097
Well, that leaves me odd man out,
doesn't it?

524
00:52:42,320 --> 00:52:44,194
- Rennie Walker.
- Jessica Bates.

525
00:52:44,364 --> 00:52:47,234
- Jessica Bates, I owe you a beer.
- Take you up on it.

526
00:52:47,409 --> 00:52:50,409
Now you take the regulator
in your right hand...

527
00:52:50,620 --> 00:52:54,534
...you take two breaths from it,
and then you give it to your partner.

528
00:52:54,708 --> 00:52:58,491
She takes two breaths from it,
and then you take it back...

529
00:52:58,670 --> 00:53:02,039
...and you breathe into it twice.

530
00:53:02,632 --> 00:53:06,416
On five, you blow out.
Don't hold her nose so tight.

531
00:53:06,594 --> 00:53:09,761
You have to close her nose,
but don't rip it off her face.

532
00:53:09,931 --> 00:53:12,256
And keep your hand on the back
of her neck.

533
00:53:12,433 --> 00:53:15,885
If her airway closes,
she will not be able to breathe.

534
00:53:16,062 --> 00:53:18,387
You're not taking this personally,
are you?

535
00:53:18,564 --> 00:53:19,975
Don't worry.
- Okay.

536
00:53:20,149 --> 00:53:22,189
Okay, that's it for this afternoon.

537
00:53:22,402 --> 00:53:26,945
Thank you for your participation.
You can all go. Thank you.

538
00:53:32,370 --> 00:53:34,493
What's your name again?

539
00:53:34,664 --> 00:53:36,039
- Rennie.
- Rennie.

540
00:53:38,376 --> 00:53:42,041
- What are you doing here?
- Oh, just hanging out.

541
00:53:42,672 --> 00:53:44,629
Spending my money.

542
00:53:51,847 --> 00:53:53,757
What are you looking at?

543
00:53:53,933 --> 00:53:58,144
Oh, I'm sorry. No, it's just that
we spent most of the day in the pool...

544
00:53:58,312 --> 00:54:01,479
...and you come out looking like that
and I look like this.

545
00:54:01,649 --> 00:54:04,104
I just wondered why that is.

546
00:54:08,114 --> 00:54:10,439
You don't look bad.

547
00:54:10,616 --> 00:54:12,110
New suit might help, though.

548
00:54:12,326 --> 00:54:17,700
Oh, it's just the suit? Great.
I'm on a budget.

549
00:54:22,920 --> 00:54:24,628
What?

550
00:54:24,797 --> 00:54:28,794
What do you say we go up to my room,
have a couple of decent drinks?

551
00:54:28,968 --> 00:54:30,213
All right.

552
00:54:35,015 --> 00:54:38,633
- You married or what?
- Nope.

553
00:54:40,771 --> 00:54:42,728
Not at the moment.

554
00:54:43,774 --> 00:54:46,479
Thank you. Who's this?

555
00:54:46,652 --> 00:54:48,360
You like that, do you?

556
00:54:48,529 --> 00:54:51,732
Men that look like this,
you usually end up supporting.

557
00:54:51,907 --> 00:54:57,779
His name's Paul Nuytten, and he owns
half a dozen hotels around the world.

558
00:54:57,955 --> 00:55:03,578
Does he have a brother? Cousin?
Young grandfather?

559
00:55:04,419 --> 00:55:07,171
He's having a party tonight.
Do you want to come?

560
00:55:07,339 --> 00:55:08,833
What?

561
00:55:09,007 --> 00:55:12,293
He's having a party tonight.
Do you want to come?

562
00:55:12,469 --> 00:55:16,336
Oh, I can't. I left all my designer
stuff back in Chicago.

563
00:55:16,515 --> 00:55:20,049
Well, that's all right.
You can borrow something of mine.

564
00:55:26,566 --> 00:55:28,808
Could I borrow your hair?

565
00:55:30,195 --> 00:55:31,855
How about your hairdresser?

566
00:55:32,531 --> 00:55:33,693
Sure.

567
00:55:43,291 --> 00:55:44,620
- You look pretty.
Thanks.

568
00:55:44,793 --> 00:55:46,453
- You gonna be okay?
- I think so.

569
00:55:46,628 --> 00:55:48,620
I'll catch you later.

570
00:55:51,633 --> 00:55:53,625
Gin and tonic.

571
00:56:01,684 --> 00:56:03,428
Thank you.

572
00:56:42,141 --> 00:56:46,602
Oh, I know this dress,
but who is the woman?

573
00:56:47,021 --> 00:56:50,604
Paul Nuytten, my new pal,
Jessica Bates.

574
00:56:50,775 --> 00:56:52,483
- Pleasure to meet you.
- Welcome.

575
00:56:52,652 --> 00:56:54,775
Thank you.
You have a beautiful home.

576
00:56:54,946 --> 00:56:56,819
Thank you.

577
00:56:58,491 --> 00:57:01,657
Would you like to dance?

578
00:57:02,244 --> 00:57:06,574
No. Thanks.
I have new shoes.

579
00:57:27,895 --> 00:57:29,971
Mademoiselle.

580
00:57:30,189 --> 00:57:32,312
Thank you. What's your name?

581
00:57:32,524 --> 00:57:36,059
- Tran.
- Tran?

582
00:57:38,947 --> 00:57:40,607
Rennie.

583
00:57:44,161 --> 00:57:46,450
Tonight you stay?

584
00:57:48,332 --> 00:57:51,286
You have a very busy day tomorrow.

585
00:57:51,460 --> 00:57:53,749
You have to polish your boat...

586
00:57:54,588 --> 00:57:56,877
...hunt some wild boar.

587
00:58:00,427 --> 00:58:02,301
Oh, Paul.

588
00:58:03,764 --> 00:58:07,097
You have your little phone book,
lots of numbers.

589
00:58:10,854 --> 00:58:13,772
Why do we keep having
this conversation?

590
00:58:14,399 --> 00:58:16,522
It's you.

591
00:58:16,693 --> 00:58:19,184
It's you I want.

592
00:58:25,327 --> 00:58:28,992
All you want is the woman
you haven't slept with.

593
00:58:29,498 --> 00:58:32,534
That's not the same as wanting me.

594
00:58:43,261 --> 00:58:44,969
Paul.

595
00:58:46,514 --> 00:58:48,388
I need a kiss.

596
00:59:23,635 --> 00:59:25,508
Fresh fish!

597
00:59:29,057 --> 00:59:32,888
Aku! Fresh aku! Aku!
Freshest fish!

598
00:59:36,939 --> 00:59:39,098
- Fish! Fish!
That one.

599
00:59:39,275 --> 00:59:41,149
- Two pounds.
Hey!

600
00:59:43,154 --> 00:59:45,727
I see you've caught your fish after all.

601
00:59:46,782 --> 00:59:49,867
Oh, can't place my face, huh?
Forgetting is useful skill.

602
00:59:50,036 --> 00:59:53,535
- I could learn some of that some time.
- Take out your cigarettes.

603
00:59:53,706 --> 00:59:56,375
Take out your cigarettes
and offer me one.

604
00:59:57,335 --> 01:00:01,379
No, thanks. This is federal government.
You don't wanna lose your license.

605
01:00:01,589 --> 01:00:03,795
Point. At the fish.

606
01:00:03,966 --> 01:00:06,089
- Say thank you and goodbye.
- Thank you.

607
01:00:06,302 --> 01:00:07,630
Goodbye.

608
01:00:15,436 --> 01:00:16,930
Who was that guy?

609
01:00:17,104 --> 01:00:20,354
He's a local, and he's asking me
if the fish is fresh.

610
01:00:26,614 --> 01:00:28,322
<i>- Hello?
Sara?</i>

611
01:00:28,490 --> 01:00:31,859
- Yes?
- Sara, it's Catharine.

612
01:00:32,036 --> 01:00:35,820
- Petersen.
- Catharine!

613
01:00:35,998 --> 01:00:39,367
It's been such a long time.
Are you all right?

614
01:00:39,585 --> 01:00:43,499
Well, I have a situation actually.

615
01:00:44,339 --> 01:00:48,171
Apparently, there's been a woman
reporter asking questions about me...

616
01:00:48,343 --> 01:00:50,003
...and Sam.

617
01:00:50,179 --> 01:00:52,717
Has anyone like that been
around to see you?

618
01:00:52,890 --> 01:00:57,801
<i>Well, yes. There was a young woman
by here about six months ago.</i>

619
01:00:58,020 --> 01:01:00,475
But she was from
the federal government.

620
01:01:02,566 --> 01:01:07,109
Listen, Sara, I really must go
right now...

621
01:01:07,279 --> 01:01:09,437
...but I'll phone you later to catch up.

622
01:01:09,615 --> 01:01:12,699
It's been a long time,
and I would like to keep in touch.

623
01:01:12,868 --> 01:01:14,362
I'll talk to you later, bye.

624
01:04:41,408 --> 01:04:44,444
I'll do it. I'll do it!

625
01:04:45,996 --> 01:04:50,040
The goddamn gauge said half full.
How come there was no air in it?

626
01:04:52,210 --> 01:04:54,618
I was supposed to check these things.

627
01:05:00,218 --> 01:05:03,753
If I was a little further out
or had my back turned...

628
01:05:04,430 --> 01:05:07,431
You scared the shit out of me.

629
01:05:09,269 --> 01:05:11,890
Thanks for not having your back turned.

630
01:05:42,009 --> 01:05:44,679
I'll be right down.

631
01:06:03,155 --> 01:06:04,947
Hey!

632
01:06:06,534 --> 01:06:09,107
You really like those things?

633
01:06:10,037 --> 01:06:12,611
My second husband was addicted.

634
01:06:12,832 --> 01:06:15,453
Second husband?
How many have you had?

635
01:06:15,626 --> 01:06:20,003
Lots. That's how I got rich.

636
01:06:20,589 --> 01:06:23,259
Once wasn't enough to get rich?

637
01:06:23,717 --> 01:06:25,840
Rich is hard.

638
01:06:26,887 --> 01:06:30,221
You never really figure
you're quite there.

639
01:06:30,808 --> 01:06:32,551
That sounds pretty romantic.

640
01:06:35,354 --> 01:06:36,932
Well...

641
01:06:38,065 --> 01:06:40,022
...I used to think of it as my job.

642
01:06:41,652 --> 01:06:44,107
Making myself appealing.

643
01:06:45,531 --> 01:06:47,903
I was a professional.

644
01:07:08,136 --> 01:07:12,798
L... I loved every one of them.

645
01:07:16,019 --> 01:07:18,012
Deeply.

646
01:07:20,315 --> 01:07:21,893
Honestly.

647
01:07:27,197 --> 01:07:29,355
It wouldn't have worked any other way.

648
01:07:37,332 --> 01:07:39,206
You like him.

649
01:07:42,921 --> 01:07:45,210
Paul. You like him.

650
01:07:49,511 --> 01:07:51,550
Go for it.

651
01:07:52,639 --> 01:07:54,678
He wants you to.

652
01:07:59,771 --> 01:08:02,096
He needs somebody now...

653
01:08:02,273 --> 01:08:04,349
...who knows how to commit.

654
01:08:09,113 --> 01:08:12,897
They're arguing over some woman
named Pelé, like the soccer player.

655
01:08:13,076 --> 01:08:16,242
One argues that she's going
on the warpath on Tuesday.

656
01:08:16,412 --> 01:08:18,654
The other guy says,
"No, next Wednesday."

657
01:08:18,831 --> 01:08:20,907
Six guys got into the same argument...

658
01:08:21,084 --> 01:08:24,951
...like they all know the same woman.
- No, no. Pelé is a goddess.

659
01:08:25,129 --> 01:08:29,875
Goddess of devastation.
She lives in a volcano. Kilauea.

660
01:08:30,051 --> 01:08:32,968
And every so often she makes fire.

661
01:08:33,137 --> 01:08:34,596
- More coffee?
- No, thanks.

662
01:08:34,764 --> 01:08:36,922
- Coffee?
No.

663
01:08:37,100 --> 01:08:40,219
Thank you.
You okay?

664
01:08:40,645 --> 01:08:44,345
I don't feel too well actually.
I think I'll go back to the hotel.

665
01:08:48,194 --> 01:08:50,732
- I'll talk to you later.
- Okay.

666
01:08:56,577 --> 01:09:00,527
- I'll drive you home.
- Don't be ridiculous.

667
01:09:00,706 --> 01:09:02,995
It's only a headache.

668
01:09:04,627 --> 01:09:08,126
I'll call you tonight.
We'll do something tomorrow.

669
01:09:08,297 --> 01:09:13,754
Look, you and Jessie
go on with your afternoon. Okay?

670
01:09:14,845 --> 01:09:16,304
And have a nice time.

671
01:09:44,458 --> 01:09:48,123
Tran, did he work
for your family in Indochina?

672
01:09:48,378 --> 01:09:49,623
Huh?

673
01:09:50,255 --> 01:09:55,629
It's just that you and he seem so close.
Did he work for another family?

674
01:09:56,470 --> 01:09:58,379
Your wife's?

675
01:10:01,308 --> 01:10:03,384
It's just that I sense...

676
01:10:04,061 --> 01:10:06,302
She was killed.

677
01:10:06,480 --> 01:10:08,887
She was only 19.

678
01:10:09,066 --> 01:10:10,560
I'm sorry.

679
01:10:12,861 --> 01:10:15,613
And I'm sorry I made you think of it.

680
01:10:16,615 --> 01:10:21,241
It's a rare gift to see things
that others cannot.

681
01:10:21,953 --> 01:10:24,871
It drives some people away.

682
01:10:26,291 --> 01:10:31,286
I don't think people like you to know
things before they're ready to tell you.

683
01:10:31,463 --> 01:10:34,998
So I should just learn
to keep my mouth shut.

684
01:10:40,639 --> 01:10:43,723
Won't you see some of the island?

685
01:10:46,686 --> 01:10:48,478
Yes, I'd like that.

686
01:11:13,046 --> 01:11:16,296
Why are you smiling?
- Because you have a look on your face.

687
01:11:16,466 --> 01:11:18,624
Look?
- Like you want to ask something...

688
01:11:18,801 --> 01:11:21,339
...then you don't.
You ought to just ask it.

689
01:11:21,512 --> 01:11:25,462
No, I was just thinking,
why hasn't this woman married?

690
01:11:25,642 --> 01:11:28,595
Attractive, intelligent.

691
01:11:28,978 --> 01:11:31,018
Very, very strong.

692
01:11:31,189 --> 01:11:34,059
- She is.
- She?

693
01:11:34,233 --> 01:11:36,060
But I'm talking about you.

694
01:11:38,237 --> 01:11:39,613
So...

695
01:11:39,781 --> 01:11:42,984
...what about you and men?

696
01:11:44,827 --> 01:11:46,238
Bad timing.

697
01:11:46,662 --> 01:11:49,497
Maybe a little bit of fear?

698
01:11:51,459 --> 01:11:53,416
Tell you something about that.

699
01:11:53,628 --> 01:11:55,751
It's very, very provocative.

700
01:13:04,406 --> 01:13:05,948
Such a strange place.

701
01:13:06,116 --> 01:13:09,615
The sap from the trees cools the lava.

702
01:13:12,706 --> 01:13:14,449
- Paul?
- Huh.

703
01:13:14,666 --> 01:13:17,916
- About Rennie.
- I'm not with Rennie.

704
01:13:18,837 --> 01:13:20,794
I'm with you.

705
01:13:23,133 --> 01:13:24,711
I can't compete with her.

706
01:13:24,885 --> 01:13:27,210
There is no necessity.

707
01:13:30,348 --> 01:13:36,517
I have to know whatever this is
is something honest and just for me.

708
01:13:37,272 --> 01:13:38,980
Look at me.

709
01:13:40,233 --> 01:13:42,107
Look at me.

710
01:13:44,154 --> 01:13:46,193
Decide.

711
01:14:10,722 --> 01:14:12,002
Here?

712
01:14:12,390 --> 01:14:16,174
I mean, can we turn
out the lights or something?

713
01:14:48,467 --> 01:14:51,552
No knock? Come into
a person's office, no knock?

714
01:14:51,721 --> 01:14:53,049
I'm sorry.

715
01:14:53,222 --> 01:14:57,968
I knock. I come to your office, I knock.
Where were you born, anyway?

716
01:14:58,144 --> 01:15:01,477
- Wisconsin. Should I come back later?
- No.

717
01:15:01,647 --> 01:15:05,230
Too late to come back later.
You already no knock.

718
01:15:05,401 --> 01:15:07,310
What you want, Wisconsin?

719
01:15:07,570 --> 01:15:11,188
Mr. Shin, my name is Rennie Walker.

720
01:15:14,076 --> 01:15:17,113
This woman befriended me.

721
01:15:17,329 --> 01:15:20,414
And now I think she's seeing my fiancé.

722
01:15:24,211 --> 01:15:25,789
I really must know.

723
01:15:26,088 --> 01:15:29,872
No, no, no. I no do this kind of work.
Not respectable.

724
01:15:30,092 --> 01:15:34,006
Mr. Shin, I'll tell you
two things about me.

725
01:15:34,179 --> 01:15:36,670
I'm very rich.

726
01:15:38,517 --> 01:15:40,842
And I'm very wealthy.

727
01:17:12,944 --> 01:17:16,894
I'm sorry about Jessie.
I thought it was what you wanted.

728
01:17:20,201 --> 01:17:23,072
Do you understand, Rennie?

729
01:17:28,710 --> 01:17:30,916
Long drive back.

730
01:17:31,963 --> 01:17:34,039
Fix me a drink?

731
01:17:57,822 --> 01:18:00,906
Rennie? Rennie?

732
01:18:02,493 --> 01:18:06,076
Come in. I want you to.

733
01:18:06,247 --> 01:18:09,616
Why tonight, after all this time?

734
01:18:09,834 --> 01:18:10,948
Huh?

735
01:18:12,461 --> 01:18:15,498
I think we've waited long enough.

736
01:19:28,870 --> 01:19:29,902
Just a minute.

737
01:19:34,292 --> 01:19:37,910
- Morning.
- Good morning.

738
01:19:45,929 --> 01:19:49,629
You left this in the Jeep
the other day.

739
01:19:49,808 --> 01:19:53,508
So you drove all the way
over just to deliver a sweater?

740
01:19:53,687 --> 01:19:55,596
No. Not exactly.

741
01:19:56,648 --> 01:20:00,942
- Would you like some coffee?
- No, thank you.

742
01:20:04,656 --> 01:20:06,483
I have something to tell you.

743
01:20:07,867 --> 01:20:09,860
Is something wrong?

744
01:20:10,620 --> 01:20:13,574
Last night, Rennie and I,
we decided to marry.

745
01:20:21,589 --> 01:20:25,005
I want you to be okay with this.

746
01:20:26,886 --> 01:20:29,175
I'll be okay.

747
01:21:02,129 --> 01:21:04,620
I'll be out there in a minute.

748
01:21:11,055 --> 01:21:12,514
Woman in love.

749
01:21:14,350 --> 01:21:19,012
- Do you really doubt it?
- No. I helped you get here, didn't I?

750
01:21:19,438 --> 01:21:22,439
When you put us together,
it made him want you more.

751
01:21:22,608 --> 01:21:25,941
So I guess you could say my
wedding gift was the groom.

752
01:21:27,530 --> 01:21:30,863
I meant it as an exchange of gifts.

753
01:21:31,909 --> 01:21:35,242
Something you could take
with you from your time with Paul.

754
01:21:35,412 --> 01:21:39,280
Well, in that case, I still owe you one.

755
01:21:42,336 --> 01:21:45,456
- That was a beautiful ceremony.
- Thank you.

756
01:21:45,631 --> 01:21:48,122
It was a lovely ceremony.

757
01:21:49,051 --> 01:21:50,675
Open it.

758
01:21:52,346 --> 01:21:55,347
Whatever this is, it means a lot to me.

759
01:22:11,657 --> 01:22:13,945
Black widow.

760
01:22:15,494 --> 01:22:17,782
She mates and she kills.

761
01:22:20,707 --> 01:22:23,494
Your question is, does she love?

762
01:22:24,753 --> 01:22:27,956
It's impossible to answer that...

763
01:22:29,007 --> 01:22:31,083
...unless you live in her world.

764
01:22:37,349 --> 01:22:40,219
Such an intriguing gift.

765
01:22:45,857 --> 01:22:48,858
Makes me wish I had
more to share with you.

766
01:22:51,071 --> 01:22:55,697
- Truth is, I'm sorry it's over.
- The truth is, it's not over yet.

767
01:23:00,080 --> 01:23:01,490
Till then.

768
01:23:03,625 --> 01:23:08,037
With your permission, may I have
the pleasure to kiss the lovely bride?

769
01:23:33,112 --> 01:23:34,939
Come in.

770
01:23:39,160 --> 01:23:42,778
Hey, Wisconsin, you knock.
I no recognize you.

771
01:23:43,247 --> 01:23:46,912
- Do you have my pictures?
- Sure.

772
01:23:47,460 --> 01:23:52,418
Hey, I see you got married
a little while ago. Congratulations.

773
01:23:54,425 --> 01:23:56,998
Good stuff, huh?

774
01:24:06,395 --> 01:24:10,227
What else do you have
in your desk, Mr. Shin?

775
01:24:10,399 --> 01:24:15,394
What do you mean by that? I got a lot
of stuff. I got paper clips. I got menthol.

776
01:24:15,571 --> 01:24:20,316
Condoms even, not it any your
business. Why you ask?

777
01:24:20,785 --> 01:24:24,699
Because you have a choice, Mr. Shin.
You can die or you can die happy.

778
01:24:24,914 --> 01:24:28,329
- Why are you doing this?
- It's in the second drawer. Look!

779
01:24:28,500 --> 01:24:30,078
You have five seconds.

780
01:24:34,798 --> 01:24:36,625
- One...
- Please.

781
01:24:37,092 --> 01:24:39,168
...two...
- Wait! Wait!

782
01:24:40,721 --> 01:24:42,548
- Hold on.
...three...

783
01:24:49,354 --> 01:24:50,683
<i>... four.</i>

784
01:24:51,982 --> 01:24:54,651
Hyland, let me see that needle.

785
01:24:56,904 --> 01:24:59,276
Get it to the lab.

786
01:24:59,490 --> 01:25:02,325
- Make sure they don't move anything.
- Okay.

787
01:25:07,289 --> 01:25:09,495
I want the whole room dusted.

788
01:25:09,666 --> 01:25:12,537
<i>Anything here for the Herald?
Or just a nothing OD?</i>

789
01:25:12,711 --> 01:25:15,416
If it gets exciting,
I'll find your number.

790
01:25:19,009 --> 01:25:20,966
Now who would you be?

791
01:25:46,620 --> 01:25:50,700
I'm glad you came over, Paul.
I need to talk to you.

792
01:25:50,874 --> 01:25:53,579
Don't you think Rennie
left a bit abruptly?

793
01:25:53,752 --> 01:25:58,746
No. Just her usual trip. She sees
her accountant on the mainland.

794
01:25:58,923 --> 01:26:00,667
Investments.

795
01:26:03,678 --> 01:26:06,714
Paul, how well do you
think you know me?

796
01:26:07,098 --> 01:26:08,129
Know you?

797
01:26:11,519 --> 01:26:14,520
- A little bit, I guess.
- Would I ever lie to you?

798
01:26:14,731 --> 01:26:17,566
- I don't know.
- Well, I did.

799
01:26:18,192 --> 01:26:20,315
My name is not Jessica Bates.

800
01:26:20,486 --> 01:26:23,357
It's Alex Barnes.
I work for the Justice Department.

801
01:26:26,326 --> 01:26:28,995
Your wife's name
is not Rennie either.

802
01:26:29,162 --> 01:26:32,495
Only, no one seems to know
what her real name is.

803
01:26:32,665 --> 01:26:34,741
- Listen to me.
- This makes no sense.

804
01:26:34,917 --> 01:26:39,663
Under three different names, she married
three different men. All wealthy men.

805
01:26:39,881 --> 01:26:43,047
- What are you trying to do?
- Paul, she killed all of them.

806
01:26:43,217 --> 01:26:48,342
She poisoned them. She's left town and
that's when they die, when she's gone.

807
01:26:52,602 --> 01:26:56,434
But she doesn't need my money.
I've seen her portfolio. Bank accounts...

808
01:26:56,606 --> 01:26:59,606
I just told you how she got them.

809
01:27:01,611 --> 01:27:04,979
- I know it sounds like I used you.
- Sounds like?

810
01:27:06,115 --> 01:27:08,606
You can't say that you
didn't know how I felt.

811
01:27:08,784 --> 01:27:12,699
That was Jessie, not some cop.

812
01:27:13,873 --> 01:27:19,377
Look, lady, don't feel so bad.
Everybody uses everybody.

813
01:27:21,464 --> 01:27:23,955
Only she does it better, right?

814
01:27:24,133 --> 01:27:27,300
That's what it is, isn't it?
She does it better.

815
01:27:27,469 --> 01:27:31,135
- No, that isn't it.
- And I told myself you could handle it.

816
01:27:31,307 --> 01:27:34,722
- I did!
- Then maybe you can explain our wills.

817
01:27:34,893 --> 01:27:39,223
They leave everything...
Everything to the Cancer Foundation.

818
01:27:39,398 --> 01:27:43,098
Nothing to each other.
It was her idea.

819
01:27:43,277 --> 01:27:46,480
Sound like the woman
you're talking about?

820
01:27:47,364 --> 01:27:49,156
Answer me!

821
01:27:55,038 --> 01:27:58,075
Tell me there is no jealousy.

822
01:27:59,668 --> 01:28:02,159
No jealousy at all.

823
01:28:25,235 --> 01:28:28,734
They said he strangled
in his sleep or something.

824
01:28:32,284 --> 01:28:34,988
Do you know a woman named
Jessica Bates?

825
01:28:35,704 --> 01:28:37,661
I do.

826
01:28:37,831 --> 01:28:42,125
It seems Miss Bates
is a federal agent named Barnes.

827
01:28:42,502 --> 01:28:47,247
And Miss Barnes believes
that you murdered Mr. Nuytten.

828
01:28:48,550 --> 01:28:51,219
Paul died last night.

829
01:28:51,386 --> 01:28:55,086
I was in San Francisco.
You can call the hotel.

830
01:28:55,306 --> 01:28:57,216
She thinks you poisoned him.

831
01:28:57,392 --> 01:29:00,808
Something that would take delayed
effect while he slept.

832
01:29:06,025 --> 01:29:08,433
- Did you check our home for the poison?
- No.

833
01:29:08,653 --> 01:29:11,773
There's no probable cause for a warrant.

834
01:29:11,948 --> 01:29:16,111
- I thought you might voluntarily...
- Of course. Yes.

835
01:29:16,286 --> 01:29:18,444
Check everything you want.

836
01:29:21,082 --> 01:29:23,620
And while you're at it...

837
01:29:24,085 --> 01:29:28,581
...Jessica Bates,
or whatever her name is...

838
01:29:29,424 --> 01:29:34,251
...was my husband's lover.
Before and after the wedding.

839
01:29:35,346 --> 01:29:38,715
So while you're searching my home...

840
01:29:41,018 --> 01:29:42,394
Interesting.

841
01:29:42,562 --> 01:29:46,974
We learned that he went to her
apartment yesterday afternoon.

842
01:30:24,478 --> 01:30:26,637
Please, have a seat.

843
01:30:28,524 --> 01:30:30,896
You've been more than kind...

844
01:30:31,318 --> 01:30:33,988
...after what you've been through.

845
01:30:36,115 --> 01:30:39,649
Listen, we did find a toxic compound
in Miss Barnes' apartment.

846
01:30:41,036 --> 01:30:43,871
Delayed-action poison.

847
01:30:44,039 --> 01:30:46,447
Also, we have certain photographs.

848
01:30:51,380 --> 01:30:54,250
Photos of Miss Barnes
and your husband.

849
01:30:54,425 --> 01:30:58,885
Those pictures are all my fault. I...

850
01:31:00,681 --> 01:31:04,180
I hired this horrid little man.

851
01:31:05,269 --> 01:31:06,811
How did you get them?

852
01:31:07,354 --> 01:31:09,927
The man you hired
is dead, Mrs. Nuytten.

853
01:31:10,107 --> 01:31:13,606
We assumed of an accidental
overdose of heroin.

854
01:31:14,528 --> 01:31:18,857
Now I'm afraid Miss Barnes has more
than just your husband to answer for.

855
01:31:22,994 --> 01:31:24,738
How well did you know him?

856
01:31:27,666 --> 01:31:29,955
Back as far as you can.

857
01:31:31,962 --> 01:31:35,128
Did you know Paul Nuytten?
Were you having a love affair?

858
01:31:36,007 --> 01:31:41,002
Mrs. Nuytten, the Cancer Foundation
flew Mr. Foster to the islands...

859
01:31:41,179 --> 01:31:44,844
...because we seem to have...
Well, something of a situation.

860
01:31:45,016 --> 01:31:49,394
- A situation?
- Yes, it's concerning Mr. Nuytten's will.

861
01:31:49,562 --> 01:31:53,856
It seems that Mr. Nuytten's legal
residence is the state of Florida.

862
01:31:54,025 --> 01:31:55,852
Were you aware of that?

863
01:31:56,027 --> 01:31:57,569
No. Should I be?

864
01:31:58,029 --> 01:32:02,738
Florida has a so-called mortmain
statute, Mrs. Nuytten.

865
01:32:03,118 --> 01:32:08,242
Any bequest to charity in a will
executed within six months of death...

866
01:32:08,414 --> 01:32:10,621
...can be invalidated by the spouse.

867
01:32:13,837 --> 01:32:15,913
- How interesting.
Of course...

868
01:32:16,089 --> 01:32:19,540
...it's no requirement
that you invalidate the gift.

869
01:32:20,718 --> 01:32:25,427
Shortly before his death,
Mr. Foster, my husband...

870
01:32:25,598 --> 01:32:29,133
...expressed reservations
about your organization.

871
01:32:31,437 --> 01:32:34,723
Profound reservations.

872
01:32:44,492 --> 01:32:48,821
Miss Barnes called from the jail.

873
01:32:50,665 --> 01:32:55,825
I tell her you plan to take long trip.

874
01:33:56,105 --> 01:33:58,430
Treating you...?

875
01:33:59,650 --> 01:34:01,025
You okay?

876
01:34:02,945 --> 01:34:05,233
I can't complain.

877
01:34:06,990 --> 01:34:09,861
It's a lot of psychological tests.

878
01:34:10,661 --> 01:34:13,496
Which I find surprising
for a crime of passion.

879
01:34:16,625 --> 01:34:19,330
Not so surprising.

880
01:34:20,504 --> 01:34:24,916
Well, they don't seem to think
your only motive was jealousy.

881
01:34:26,843 --> 01:34:28,635
Not of Paul, anyway.

882
01:34:29,513 --> 01:34:33,261
They seem to think
your obsession was...

883
01:34:34,726 --> 01:34:36,220
...with me.

884
01:34:36,937 --> 01:34:40,270
They think you started out as
an ambitious federal agent...

885
01:34:42,317 --> 01:34:45,686
...and you became obsessed by this...

886
01:34:46,738 --> 01:34:48,731
...phantom.

887
01:34:49,407 --> 01:34:51,483
And then...

888
01:34:52,160 --> 01:34:54,153
...you chased her...

889
01:34:55,080 --> 01:34:56,657
...and you chased her...

890
01:34:58,249 --> 01:35:02,377
...and when you thought you'd
never be quick enough to catch her...

891
01:35:02,545 --> 01:35:04,372
I killed him...

892
01:35:04,756 --> 01:35:06,748
...to frame you.

893
01:35:34,118 --> 01:35:36,241
How did you manage it?

894
01:35:36,412 --> 01:35:39,366
What, did you leave town
and sneak back?

895
01:35:40,750 --> 01:35:44,201
Did you use the same bottle
you put in my place?

896
01:35:44,378 --> 01:35:48,672
You always did have a tendency
to over-think things.

897
01:35:49,383 --> 01:35:54,211
The most important thing about figuring
anything out is knowing when to stop.

898
01:36:01,103 --> 01:36:03,143
You know...

899
01:36:04,649 --> 01:36:08,516
...of all the relationships
I'll look back on...

900
01:36:08,694 --> 01:36:10,936
...in 50 years' time...

901
01:36:15,117 --> 01:36:18,866
...I'll always remember this one.

902
01:36:38,265 --> 01:36:39,973
Hello, Sara.

903
01:36:42,770 --> 01:36:44,312
It's good to see you.

904
01:37:12,883 --> 01:37:16,216
I put the poison in Paul's brandy.
You mustn't...

905
01:37:16,386 --> 01:37:18,712
We know. We found it before he did.

906
01:38:27,915 --> 01:38:29,659
Get your cameras, she's here!

907
01:38:29,834 --> 01:38:34,579
Congratulations, that was a brilliant trap.
Are you going back to Washington now?

908
01:38:34,756 --> 01:38:37,081
Were you tipped off
she was here in Hawaii?

909
01:38:37,258 --> 01:38:39,251
Please, give us an answer for the press.

910
01:38:39,427 --> 01:38:42,381
Are you going to testify at the trial?

911
01:38:45,933 --> 01:38:48,140
I will give you the statement.